Nigerian Army troops of 17th Brigade in Katsina State have rescued six kidnaped victims from Danmusa local government council of the state. Presenting the victims to the State government, Major Emmanuel Adebayo who represented the Brigade Commander said the bandits abducted eleven victims but the troops were able to rescue 6 persons but are yet to trace the whereabouts of the remaining persons. Meanwhile, suspected armed bandits have invaded Karare village in Batseri local government area of Katsina state and abducted two married women and a little child. Eye witness said the bandits stormed the village at about 12:20am yesterday with sophisticated weapons. They first attacked the house of Ciroma Karare and as they attempted to kill him, his daughter cried out and pleaded with them to let her father go, but she was taken away instead. His words, “On 23/06/2020 at about 12:20am, a group of armed bandit/kidnappers with dangerous weapons attacked karare village in Batsari local government and kidnaped a 23-year-old married woman with her little child as well as 20-year-old Saudatu Ahmad, the daughter of Ciroma Karare. He also added that the hoodlums dropped a Glo phone number for the victim’s families to contact them. Similarly, a day before the present attack, another source also revealed that at about 1:24pm, a group of bandits on motorcycles numbering about eight also attacked Batseri Dan Alhaji, where they rustled six cattles from the house of one Saleh Garawa. The State police command through its spokesman, Gambo Isah denied the incident as he said bandits cannot attack in a broad day light and that journalists should always verify information before going to press.